🚀 Day 04 — Linux Package Management & System Monitoring

Today we will learn how Linux systems install software, monitor resources, and check system information — essential skills for every DevOps Engineer.

📦 What is Package Management?

Package management helps install, update, remove, and manage software in Linux.

Instead of downloading .exe files like Windows, Linux uses package managers.

🐧 Common Linux Package Managers
Distribution	Package Manager
Ubuntu / Debian	apt
CentOS / RHEL	yum / dnf
📥 1. apt — Package Manager (Ubuntu/Debian)
📌 Definition

apt is used to:

Install software
Update packages
Remove packages
🔄 Update Package List
sudo apt update

📡 Downloads latest package information.

⬆️ Upgrade Installed Packages
sudo apt upgrade

📦 Updates installed software.

📥 Install Package
Example — Install Nginx
sudo apt install nginx
❌ Remove Package
sudo apt remove nginx
🔍 Search Package
apt search docker
🐧 2. yum — Package Manager (CentOS/RHEL)
📌 Definition

yum manages software packages in RedHat-based systems.

📥 Install Package
sudo yum install nginx
🔄 Update Packages
sudo yum update
❌ Remove Package
sudo yum remove nginx
💽 3. df — Disk Space Usage
📌 Definition

Displays filesystem disk usage.

🛠️ Syntax
df -h

📖 -h = human-readable format

✅ Example Output
Filesystem      Size  Used Avail Use%
/dev/sda1        50G   20G   28G  42%
📂 4. du — Directory Size
📌 Definition

Shows file and directory size.

🛠️ Syntax
du -sh folder-name
✅ Example
du -sh logs

Output:

120M logs
🧠 5. free — Memory Usage
📌 Definition

Displays RAM and swap memory usage.

🛠️ Syntax
free -h
✅ Example Output
Mem:   2.0Gi  1.2Gi  500Mi
⚡ 6. top — System Monitoring
📌 Definition

Displays running processes and system usage in real time.

Shows:

CPU usage
RAM usage
Running processes
🛠️ Syntax
top
🔴 Exit Top

Press:

q
🖥️ 7. uname — System Information
📌 Definition

Displays Linux system information.

🛠️ Syntax
uname -a
✅ Example Output
Linux ubuntu 5.15.0 x86_64 GNU/Linux
🌐 8. hostname — System Hostname
📌 Definition

Displays system hostname.

🛠️ Syntax
hostname
✅ Example
ubuntu-server
🧪 Hands-On Practice

Run these commands:

df -h

free -h

uname -a

hostname

top
📦 Real DevOps Scenario
Install Nginx Web Server
Step 1️⃣ Update Packages
sudo apt update
Step 2️⃣ Install Nginx
sudo apt install nginx
Step 3️⃣ Verify Service
systemctl status nginx
Step 4️⃣ Check Server IP
hostname -I
🔥 Why This Matters in DevOps

DevOps Engineers constantly monitor:

💽 Disk usage
🧠 Memory usage
⚡ CPU load
📦 Installed software
🌐 Server details

These commands are used daily in:

AWS EC2
Docker containers
Kubernetes nodes
Production servers
🎯 Important Commands Summary
Command	Purpose
